The paper deals with the construction of a trapezoidal-map search-structure for planar point location, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses the depth of the history DAG and its correspondence to the trapezoidal search tree, which are data structures used in computational geometry, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper involves the analysis of the expected preprocessing time, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions the use of randomization, which could suggest it belongs to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with planar maps induced by finite collections of pairwise interior disjoint well-behaved curves, which could place it in cs.GR (Graphics).
